flowRoot.flowPara: CourtListener.com aims to ease the difficulty of staying up to date with court documents by providing a free and open source platform for the aggregation, organization, search and retrieval of legal documents. The aggregation of new court documents is completed by a custom-designed web crawler on a rolling basis, building a huge corpus, and providing the latest cases from the Federal Courts of Appeal within – on average – about fifteen minutes from the moment they are published on the court website. From there, the documents are quickly indexed and Atom feeds and document listings are updated. Finally, at the user's option, alerts are emailed either daily, weekly, or monthly informing them about the documents that matched their alert queries.
